task.summary: Default task
Implemented actually painting buttons and showing which ones are recommended.
Added a border to the menu buttons
Started optimizing the menu. UNSTABLE
Menu optimized, simple building from packages implemented.
Added some buttons and some documentation
Added randomly generated maps.
Started with pathfinding and updated readme drastically. Added a test robot for testing pathfinding.
Updated .gitignore
Merged developing to master
Quick test update.
Improved pathfinding, now doesn't jitter and moves diagonally. Added an indicator for when blocks cannot be mined (a cross on the mining cursor.
Fixed pathfinding from ore to launchers.
Backup commit, probably broken
Added Factories, building ore mines, furnaces and launchers create a resource system using the pathfinding of robots.
Made robots traveling between factories much smoother and prettier.

Updated factories to be able to send goods even if it is collidable. Robots now don't get stuck when their path gets completely blocked and instead self-destruct so that their home can send a new robot.
Renamed a bunch of tiles and fixed a bug where the robot gets stuck at the deliver position if it's blocked in.
Added package generation. Requires a ore mine, furnace and a package factory on the map.
Forgot some textures.
Bugfixes for Linux
Fixed what seemed to be a heisenbug and started on custom targets for tiles.
Made sure destroying a factory destroys its corresponding robots.
Fixed movement, now works as before, but with vectors instead of four variables.
Fixed movement for packages and robots too.
Added functionality for selecting custom delivery targets for your factories that send things. They will prioritize those tiles over others. This is done with the W key.

Added a requests system that allows robots to distribute resources more evenly among multiple targets. Changed the structure of the folder layout a bit to help the IDE I'm using to know what file I mean when I reference objects. Rearranged Robot code a bit from PathingEntity to Robot.
Added batteries.
Added launcher rotation.
Added launchers shooting rockets that destroy collidable tiles including rocks. Moved Robot to units.py. Rockets explode at a kind of stupid timing though.
